&lt;h1 id="if-youre-so-smart-why-arent-you-happy"&gt;If You&amp;rsquo;re So Smart, Why Aren&amp;rsquo;t You Happy?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feb 12 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can increase your happiness without losing your drive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Happiness is for stupid people.&amp;rdquo; That&amp;rsquo;s a common complaint I hear from smart overachievers. They think only dumb or lazy people can be happy. Entrepreneurs will say, &amp;ldquo;I don&amp;rsquo;t want to be happy because I want to be successful.&amp;rdquo; They worry that if they get too happy they&amp;rsquo;ll lose their desire and won&amp;rsquo;t work hard anymore.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Desire Is a Contract You Make to Be Unhappy</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/desire-is-a-contract-you-make-to-be-unhappy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 10 Feb 2020 15:39:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/desire-is-a-contract-you-make-to-be-unhappy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/naval/zh/desire-is-a-contract-you-make-to-be-unhappy.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
